# Accessibility Standards

## Color Contrast
- **WCAG AA Compliance:** Ensure 4.5:1 contrast ratio for normal text, 3:1 for large text
- **Theme Variables:** Use semantic color variables that maintain proper contrast
- **Testing:** Test both light and dark modes for contrast compliance

## Focus Management
- **Focus Indicators:** Use `focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-primary/50` pattern
- **Keyboard Navigation:** Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible
- **Focus Trapping:** Implement proper focus management in modals and forms

## Screen Reader Support
- **Semantic HTML:** Use proper heading hierarchy (h1, h2, h3)
- **ARIA Labels:** Add appropriate ARIA labels for complex interactions
- **Skip Links:** Include skip-to-content links as defined in [globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css)

## Motion & Animation
- **Reduced Motion:** Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` setting
- **Smooth Transitions:** Use `transition-colors` for color changes
- **Performance:** Keep animations performant and purposeful

## Form Accessibility
- **Labels:** Always associate labels with form controls
- **Error Messages:** Use `text-destructive` for clear error indication
- **Loading States:** Provide clear loading feedback with `text-muted-foreground`

## Touch Targets
- **Minimum Size:** Ensure interactive elements are at least 44px (2.75rem)
- **Spacing:** Provide adequate spacing between touch targets
- **Button Sizing:** Use `min-height: 2.5rem` as defined in component styles
